<h2>What are Cookies?</h2>
<p>
    Cookies are text files that are placed on your computer or handheld device (such as smartphones and tablets) when you visit certain pages on the Internet.
    They are used to remember when your computer or device accesses a website. Cookies are stored in your browser and help the website to recognise your device
    the next time you visit. Most cookies will not collect information that directly identifies you as a person, and will instead collect more general information, such 
    as how visitors arrive at our website. Cookies may, however, be used to create a profile of the visitor’s activities on the Internet which, for example,
    can be used to try and predict your purchasing and behavioral preferences.
</p>
<br />

<h2>Types of Cookies</h2>

<h3>Temporary Cookies</h3>

<p>
    Session cookies are stored only temporarily during a browsing session and are deleted from the user’s device when the browser is closed.
</p>

<h3>Persistent Cookies</h3>

<p>
    Persistent cookies used on our website generally have a maximum lifespan of thirty (30) days; please see “Cookie Declaration” section below.
</p>

<h3>First Party Cookies</h3>

<p>
    First party cookies are set by the website you are visiting, and they can only be read by that site.
</p>

<h2>Cookie Categories</h2>

<h3>Necessary Cookies</h3>

<p>
    Necessary cookies are required for the operation of our website, such as to ensure security. 
    For example, certain cookies enable you to log into secure areas of the CCH website. These cookies do 
    not require your consent and cannot be switched off. You can set your browser to block or alert you 
    about these cookies, but some parts of our website may not work if you block these types of cookies.
</p>

<h3>Functional Cookies</h3>

<p>
    Functional cookies are used to provide certain functionalities to you by recognising you when you 
    return to the CCH website so that we can offer you a better experience on this website. For instance, 
    these cookies help us to personalise our content for you, greet you by name, and remember your preferences 
    (for example, your choice of colours and fonts, or to set a cookie to store your preferences regarding 
    the cookies on our website).
</p>

<h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>

<p>
    Analytics cookies allow us to analyse CCH website usage and understand how visitors use it. These 
    cookies recognise and collect information about the number of visitors, the pages they view, how long 
    they view pages for, and how they move around the website while using it. This helps us improve the way
    our website works, for example, by ensuring that visitors are easily finding what they are looking for. 
    If you do not consent to these types of cookies, we are unable to improve the CCH website based on 
    information from your visit.
</p>
