<h2>Managing Cookies and Withdrawing Consent</h2>

<p>
    We will obtain your opt-in consent to the use of cookies when you first access the CCH website, and 
    on the introduction of any new cookies, unless they are necessary cookies in which your consent is not 
    required. When you visit our website and go to the ‘Accessibility’ a popup is displayed asking you to 
    “Accept Cookies” or “Decline Nonessential Cookies” and notifies you that you must accept cookies to 
    enable the accessibility features. You can then accept all cookies, or you may refuse cookies (except 
    those that are necessary).
</p>
<p>
    If you reject cookies, we will not set those cookies on your device, except necessary cookies, and set 
    a cookie to remember that you do not want any nonessential cookies to set when you visit the website.
</p>
<p>
    If you have accepted cookies but later decide you want to reject them (withdraw your consent) for the future, 
    you can update your preferences related to the cookies operating on our website by clicking the button on the 
    ‘Accessibility’ page.
</p>
<p>
    You can also disable cookies by changing your browser settings to reject cookies. How to do this depends 
    on the browser you are using. All modern browsers allow you to change your cookie settings that will 
    typically be found in the ‘options’ or ‘preferences’ menu of your browser. Use the ‘Help’ option in your 
    browser for more details.
</p>
